msgid "Client Suggested Identity Provider"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "OIDC applications can bypass the {project_name} login page by specifying a hint on which identity provider they want to use."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "This is done by setting the `kc_idp_hint` query parameter in the Authorization Code Flow authorization endpoint."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "{project_name} OIDC client adapters also allow you to specify this query parameter when you access a secured resource at the application."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "For example"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"GET /myapplication.com?kc_idp_hint=facebook HTTP/1.1\n"
"Host: localhost:8080\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "In this case, is expected that your realm has an identity provider with an alias `facebook`. If this provider doesn't exist the login form will be displayed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "If you are using `keycloak.js` adapter, you can also achieve the same behavior:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#, no-wrap
msgid "var keycloak = new Keycloak('keycloak.json');\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"keycloak.createLoginUrl({\n"
"\tidpHint: 'facebook'\n"
"});\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "The `kc_idp_hint` query parameter also allows the client to override the default identity provider if one is configured for the `Identity Provider Redirector` authenticator. The client can also disable the automatic redirecting by setting the `kc_idp_hint` query parameter to an empty value."
msgstr ""
